race.comment: REGAL HUNTER (4) trialled well before being nudged out here on debut. Looks suited over the longer sprint and with the extra fitness he can go one better. EAGLEFURTHER (5) switched from a Victorian yard and led and was outsprinted late here over a mile on a two-week return. Maps well and has a senior hoop on today. Comes back 200m and should be in the finish. LEO DAVINCI (3) resumes with a solid effort and he has placed second up. His best efforts would see him competitive. ARCADE BOY (1) gives away starts, but he resumed with a promising effort before disappointing back a touch in trip. The in-form Byrne Burke rides for the first time and we may see a better effort.
